{"by":"internet_points","id":47775896,"parent":47773812,"text":"Then I sincerely hope my bank and doctor and government offices are all free-riders.<p>Dependency cooldowns, like staged update rollouts, mean less brittleness &#x2F; more robustness in that not every part of society is hit at once. And the fact that cooldowns are not evenly distributed is a <i>good thing</i>. Early adopters and vibe coders take more chances, banks should take less.<p>But yeah, upload queues also make sense. We should have both!","time":1776239153,"type":"comment"}